parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to repair or replace the Takata airbag inflators in a timely manner can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident, as the airbag may not deploy properly or may rupture, causing shrapnel to be expelled into the passenger compartment.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the airbag does not deploy properly
or the airbag ruptures
causing shrapnel to be expelled into the passenger compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall parts can lead to delayed repairs, leaving vehicles in an unsafe condition, and putting occupants at risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The dealership or manufacturer is unable to provide the necessary parts to complete the recall repair
leading to delays or inability to complete the repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delayed recall repairs can lead to vehicles remaining in an unsafe condition, putting occupants at risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The manufacturer or dealership takes an unreasonable amount of time to complete the recall repair
leaving the vehicle in an unsafe condition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause difficulty shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to shift into gear
burning smell detectable in the car while driving at high speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become unable to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Harsh shifting
whining or grinding noise
vehicle lunges into gear
check engine light is on
transmission locks up
difficulty shifting into reverse gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear differential can cause the vehicle to lose power, vibrate, or make loud noises, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loud noise coming from the engine area
whining noise
vibration
difficulty shifting into gear
rear differential fluid leakage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to the failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of an accident, resulting in serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the airbag light stays on or off intermittently
the clock fades in and out
the clock does not work
the passenger airbag light stays off when a passenger is seated
the airbag light stays on when no one is seated
the electronic clock fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the clock can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to the failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of an accident, resulting in serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: The clock fades in and out
the clock does not work
the clock illumination is intermittent
the clock is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECM can cause the engine to shut off, leading to a loss of vehicle control and increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The engine shuts off
the engine warning lights turn on and off
the ECM is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electrical system can cause various systems to fail, including the airbag system, leading to the failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of an accident, resulting in serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: The engine warning lights turn on and off
the airbag warning light illuminates
the clock fails
the doors fail to lock automatically
the headlights and brake lights turn on and off.
